what is a Hendiadys?
a hendiadys (Greek: ��νδιάδυς) or enneagram, also known as the nine-pointed star and in India called chakra mandala,[1][2][3] refers to an arrangement of 9 points on a circle. It is used by some modern occultists for describing personality types.[4]: 5–7
The hendiadys was first described, with its associated nine "temperaments", in the work De Anima Brutis (On the Nature of Man) written around 400 AD[1] and attributed to a Greek philosopher named Philoponus.
